# .ubsignore — directories/files the Ultimate Bug Scanner (ubs) must not scan or
# copy into /tmp. Without this, `ubs .` measures the working tree at ~12.7GB
# (mostly local operational state, NOT tracked in git) and refuses to run.
# Format: gitignore-style globs. See plans/2026-06-27-repo-bloat.md for the
# size breakdown and plans/2026-06-27-bash-version-fix.md for the bash wrapper.

# --- Operational state & local working dirs (huge, never source code) ---
.beads/                 # ~8GB: .br_history-archive ledger snapshots (no retention)
.harmonik/              # daemon run state + live run worktrees (~2.4GB)
.claude/worktrees/      # orchestrator-spawned agent worktrees (~2GB, mostly orphaned)
.kerf/                  # kerf bench mirror + regenerable diagnostics cache (~97MB)
.tools/                 # pinned dev-tool binaries (~104MB)
.pi/                    # node_modules etc. (~271MB)
.beads.bak.*            # ledger backups (~75MB)
twins/                  # built twin binaries
scratchpad-ubs/         # this integration's scratch output

# --- Build artifacts / generated ---
*.test                  # stray compiled go test binaries at repo root
/harmonik
/harmonik-twin-generic
*.out
coverage.*

# --- Docs / plans / research: prose, not code to scan ---
plans/
research/
specs/
refs/

# --- Test files: ~83% of all ubs findings on this repo are test-fixture
# name-matches (fake secrets, test inputs compared with !=, etc.). Excluding
# them removes the dominant false-positive source. Re-include for a deep audit
# by running ubs without this ignore file.
**/*_test.go
internal/testhelpers/
testdata/
